This paper belongs to the field of Evolution Strategies, which is a subfield of Computational Intelligence and Optimization. The paper specifically analyzes the performance of a $(1,\lambda)$-Evolution Strategy on a linear constraint optimization problem, which falls under the category of Numerical Optimization (cs.NE). The paper also uses Markov chain analysis to study the stability and convergence of the algorithm, which is related to the field of Dynamical Systems (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper uses resampling and adaptive step-size control, which are techniques commonly used in Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and control also relates to the field of Systems and Control (cs.SY).
